---

1. The Body Is the First Receiver
Before thought, before language, before interpretation —  
the body reacts.

Not spiritually.  
Not magically.  
Just biologically.

The body is the first layer of signal detection:

- breath shifts  
- core tightens  
- skin activates  
- temperature changes  
- attention sharpens  

This is the pre‑verbal signal.

---

2. Sensation Is Not Story
The body fires before the mind explains.

Sensation is:

- raw  
- immediate  
- unfiltered  
- honest  

Story is:

- interpretation  
- meaning  
- narrative  
- context  

Embodied Signal keeps these lanes clean.

The body speaks first.  
The mind translates second.

---

3. The Core as Stabilizer
You’ve described this since childhood:

- pressure in the stomach  
- the “ball” or “charge”  
- the brace  
- the release  
- the second wind  

This is not adrenaline on command.  
This is interoceptive literacy — awareness of internal signals most people never notice.

The core is the anchor of the embodied signal.

---

4. The Chills and Pings as Alignment Markers
When meaning lands:

- goosebumps  
- cold surges  
- scalp activation  
- hair lift  
- micro‑twitches  

These are not supernatural.  
These are somatic markers of coherence.

The body is saying:

> “This matches the pattern.”

Embodied Signal treats these as data, not destiny.

---

5. The Breath Clause
Breath is the regulator between:

- resonance  
- clarity  
- pressure  
- action  

A steady breath stabilizes the signal.  
A disrupted breath distorts it.

Embodied Signal uses breath as the bridge between body and mind.

---

6. The Integration Rule
A signal is only valid when:

- the body reacts  
- the mind recognizes  
- the structure holds  

If any layer fails, the signal is incomplete.

Embodied Signal ensures:

- no over‑reliance on sensation  
- no over‑reliance on thought  
- no over‑reliance on emotion  

All three must align.

---

7. Signature Line
The body receives.  
The mind interprets.  
The signal becomes truth only when both agree.

— Codex.Embodied.Signal.v001

